value.value: any anomaly of the band of mesoderm located between the segmented paraxial mesoderm and the lateral plate mesoderm, that develops into the nephrogenic cord

anomaly in the amount of mineral per square centimeter of bone (usually g/cm2), used as a measure of structural strength and screen for osteoporosis; bone mineral density is the ratio of bone mineral content to bone size
any anomaly in the amount (usually in grams/cm) of bone mineral divided by a bone-scanned area
elevation in the amount (usually in grams/cm) of bone mineral divided by a bone-scanned area
reduction in the amount (usually in grams/cm) of bone mineral divided by a bone-scanned area

an abnormally increased amount of space occupied by blood in the vessels
an abnormally decreased amount of space occupied by blood in the vessels

label.value: increased DN1 thymic pro-T cell number

label.value: decreased DN1 thymic pro-T cell number

increased number of thymocytes that have the cell surface marker phenotype CD4-negative, CD8-negative, CD44-positive, and CD25-positive

definition.value: Note that this type of thymocyte is at the earliest stage of T cell receptor rearrangement of the beta, gamma, and delta T cell receptor chains.

value.value: reduced number of thymocytes that have the cell surface marker phenotype CD4-negative, CD8-negative, CD44-positive, and CD25-positive

definition.value: Note that this type of thymocyte is at the earliest stage of T cell receptor rearrangement of the beta, gamma, and delta T cell receptor chains.

reduced number of thymocytes that have the cell surface marker phenotype CD4-negative, CD8-negative, CD44-positive, and CD25-negative and expressing the T cell receptor beta-chain in complex with the pre-T cell receptor alpha chain.
increased number of thymocytes that have the cell surface marker phenotype CD4-negative, CD8-negative, CD44-negative, CD25-negative, and pre-TCR-positive.

definition.value: Note that this type of thymocyte has passed the beta-selection checkpoint and is rapidly proliferating and beginning to rearrange the T cell receptor alpha chain.

value.value: reduced number of thymocytes that have the cell surface marker phenotype CD4-negative, CD8-negative, CD44-negative, CD25-negative, and pre-TCR-positive.

definition.value: Note that this type of thymocyte has passed the beta-selection checkpoint and is rapidly proliferating and beginning to rearrange the T cell receptor alpha chain.

derangement of the normal pattern of the layered structure of the cuticle, cortex and/or medulla of a hair

any structural anomaly of the cord-like structure in males comprising the vas deferens and associated tissue that runs from the abdomen down to each testis
